SIMPLE: poling
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Poling
<hw>Pol"ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From <er>Pole</er> a
stick.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of supporting or of propelling by
means of a pole or poles; <as>as, the <ex>poling</ex> of beans; the
<ex>poling</ex> of a boat.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Gardening)</fld> <def>The operation of dispersing
worm casts over the walks with poles.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>One of the poles or planks used in upholding the
side earth in excavating a tunnel, ditch, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Polish</ent>⟦br⟧
